snippet.title: Penang is Home.
snippet.description:
This is a view of Penang - home - in the eyes of a kid returning from UK to Malaysia, to remember home forever and always, no matter where they go.

- - -
Author's note:

3 weeks into an 8 minute video and I still am not satisfied because there is supposed to be a 3rd part of this vid but my video editing software (yours truly, windows movie maker) decided to crash on me oh la da dee :( .... Therefore, the abrupt end.

Also what was supposed to showcase "home" suddenly became a 70% food video - cause Penang has amazingly good food and food showcases our insane culture so well!!

Song credits: 
Vexento - Home
http://soundcloud.com/vexento
The Greatest Showman - From Now On (Pitched up)

snippet.title: CRAZY RICH ASIANS - Yellow 流星 Cover (Katherine Ho)
snippet.description:
It was really fun figuring out this song by ear! Kept replaying the song lots and I think this is 90% accurate as the song is, including all the weird 7th and sustain chords - hopefully! 

Also noisy leaf blower from like 2 minutes onwards, and I keep saying 尽 as 书 cause the 繁体 mandarin looks like 書 lol (reading the lyrics that's why I keep looking left!!)

P/S: Not a singer at all, this is just for fun YAY ^_______^ 

Song Title: Yellow / 流星
Artist: Katherine Ho
Movie: Crazy Rich Asians / 瘋狂亞洲富豪
Year: 2018 
Guitar Arrangement: Meeee :DD

snippet.title: Moana - How Far I'll Go (MY ORCHESTRAL VERSION)
snippet.description:
I. FINALLY. FINISHED. MAKING THIS!!!!

To the Moana fandom & my dad, this is my cover of Moana’s “How Far I’ll Go”, in ORCHESTRAL version!!!

I apologize in advance for the lack of mixing! It’s best when heard with headphones, still though :)

This was made purely using my imagination, no piano sheets and no instrument samples - so I’m sorry in advance for any mistakes!!

I really loved sampling the sound effects though - Moana’s voice, the Cheehoo, the waveees ^_^ It was fun!!! still this took so looong to make oh goshh

- - -
If you like this song and would like to request a song of your own / make a contribution for me to go on my volunteering expedition, click here! http://justgiving.com/kiddai

Hear on soundcloud here!
https://m.soundcloud.com/wingardiums/moana :D

snippet.description:

The song name is called "TRUST". What a great name!
Also thank you Gem Mitchell for providing us the download link for the .wav file to the original song! You are awesome! (https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_S3RTREVS4NcWI5Y09VWHlaWFE)

snippet.title: HTTYD 2 - Flying With Mother (Piano Cover)
snippet.description:
For Qian, Yunwei and Yunying, who went to see How To Train Your Dragon 2 with me! =D

Hear the soundtrack of Flying With Mother here! - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=asjzZ0-Zk8Y

Pardon my mistakes - I did it entirely by ear. I really think John Powell made a massive improvement in his score for HTTYD2! This is such a wonderful theme for the movie and I felt like soaring once hearing it ^-^ 

This piano cover is inspired by @supershigi who did her own rendition of this song too! Check it out at http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2fn8wsSyOEQ ! Sorry for the random cuts at some parts though, cause I kinda screwed up, haha.

snippet.title: Eddie Van Der Meer - Path To The Unknown (Cover)
snippet.description:
P/S: You might want to crank up the volume a little, it's pretty soft! Also, sorry for the buzzy strings and accidental wrong notes, I did this entirely by ear =D

See the original song here! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cNbiUMuy6yA

This is for JY, D, J, A and R - you know who you are! And for Eddie too, for creating the most wonderful fingerstyle piece that absolutely talks to my soul.

I decided to make a cover of this song because, in my entire life, there are only two instrumental tracks who absolutely speak to the depths of my soul - John Powell's "Forbidden Friendship" and now.... this song, "Path To The Unknown". Eddie Van Der Meer told me a story through this song without words, but he was able to convey it all. I don't know about you guys, but it spoke to me that the unknown was a mysterious thing that, once we try to grasp hold of it, it dissipates into thin air, leaving you to ask yourself questions. It's the mere thought of what was and will be, the mere fantasy of conjuring an image, so powerful that could make you shudder or admire in awe at what would be... or not? That is the unknown. 

There was a time where I was heavily plunged into the unknown, afraid to venture in it. I was scared of what will be, and afraid I would cause more damage if I did anything. Then these guys came, and one by one they pulled me out - oh my gods how they actually changed me into a better person - and this is why I decided to dedicate this to them.

Because of them, my path to the unknown became clear ^-^

snippet.title: Happy Birthday Christina!! :D - Pyramid And Just A Dream REMIX
snippet.description:
SORRY I'M LATE!!! Dad took us on a trip for two whole days so I couldn't finish this on time! 

This is a vid I made for Christina Grimmie, one of my inspirations. 
It's a remix of Charice Ft. Iyaz - Pyramid and the cover of Just A Dream by Sam Tsui, Kurt Schneider and yes, Christina Grimmie herself. 
YOU GO CHRIS :D

This is my first attempt on remixing and I would appreciate any positive/negative comments on this vid =D 

You can download the mp3 for this here http://www.mediafire.com/?ddsb977x7cdgoba 

Credits go to Emily for brainblasting me! 

Once again, HAPPY BIRTHDAY CHRISTINA!!
